      • initFilterArray

        protected static com.guidewire.pl.system.filters.BeanBasedQueryFilter[] initFilterArray(com.guidewire.pl.system.locale.DisplayKey displayKey,
                                                                     int beanCount)
        Set up the array needed to contain filters. Usually allocates an array of (beanCount + 1) to store each filter which will be created. The extra slot is for the "All" filter. If no items or only one filter item (for 0 or 1 bean, resp.) would later be created, a single-element array with only the "All" filter is produced.
        Parameters:
        displayKey - the label for the "All" filter entry.
        beanCount - the number of beans, which matches the number of filters.
        Returns:
        a BeanBasedQueryFilter array which is sized for the correct number of filters.
